title: Lovely Idea, shame the app is now unstable
comment: I updated my phone firmware today and now the app keeps crashing when I try to start a call. It is a nice idea and when it was working it was very well integrated. I hope these issues can be overcome soon.

title: Not sure about this yet
comment: New moto g 1st gen phone with droid  4.4.4 app crashes on verification screen every time

title: Android 5 incompatible?
comment: Nice app, but after I've updated to Android 5.0.1 it started giving me "incorrect MMI code", making me unable to call. Uninstalled until update and fix are made.

title: in the land (UK) where Invasion of Privacy is the RULE...
comment: ... show me the 3rd-party code audit of this app & provider concluding that there are NO BACKDOORS built-in. otherwise, sticking with more trusted alternatives (CSipSimple) that don't update every 5 days.

title: This is the best SIP/VIOP App for android.
comment: This App has no contenders or competition. Open source. Looks for voip address for every number you dial. There is nothing quite like it.

title: sends international sms, then simply doesn't work
comment: This SIP phone pops up an activation screen with no way to back out. In order to make it do anything at all, I had to verify my phone number with sip5060.net. Well, this wouldn't be a problem if it didn't validate the account by sending an international text message, which I only found out after receiving my cell phone bill. Even worse, once my account was verified, although I can apparently make calls, I hear no sound at all. It would seem that this app is to be avoided.

title: Geek oriented
comment: Does not have include/exclude patterns to automate selection

title: Works with Asterisk
comment: I was really frustrated that viber doesn't work with Asterisk.  Lumicall does work well though, thanks for providing an open app for mobile voip.

title: very easy to use
comment: Lumicall is very easy to install and use.  Having the walkie-talkie function is an extra bonus I did not expect, but now we use it around the house like an intercom.

title: Excellent audio on Galaxy Tab
comment: The Galaxy Tab is sold without support for making phone calls - but installing this app allows it to make calls, and the quality is better than from my normal phone. Some of the early versions of this app were a little bit rough around the edges, but it seems OK now using v1.4

title: Fc all the time
comment: Force closes when trying to set up custom SIP data.
